# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
Not sure sorry..

### Is this a regression?
Not sure sorry..

### Description

When inside custom.component.scss, css encapsulation with auto-assigned angular data-attribute does not works as intended when the escaped character includes a colon.


REPRODUCTION

```
// this works even with css encapsulation
.custom\/red {
    padding: 20px;
    background: red;
}

// however this doesn't work
.custom\:blue {
    padding: 20px;
    background: blue;
}
```

WHAT IS EXPECTED

```
.custom\/red[_ngcontent-sno-c1] {
    padding: 20px;
    background: red;
}

.custom\:blue[_ngcontent-sno-c1] {
    padding: 20px;
    background: blue;
}
```

WORKAROUND

Workaround to solve this is to turn css encapsulation.

## üåç  Your Environment

Angular 8

