### Description

If I build the angular app without i18n everything is ok, but If I use i18n all @font-face font paths aren't prefixed with the language.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
Add Roboto ttf font to assets folder, then add to styles.scss

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Roboto-Regular';
  font-style: normal;
  font-weight: normal;
  src: url('/assets/Roboto-Regular.ttf') format('truetype');
}
Use this font somewhere in the app.

Now build the app with "ng build --prod --aot" and load it with a very basic expressjs server like this one:

```
var express = require('express');
var app = express();

app.use(express.static('public'));

app.listen(3000, function() {
  console.log('Example app listening on port 3000!');
});
```

Then add i18n to the app and build the app with english language, so the app will be exposed at localhost:3000/en and the expressjs server will be something like this:

```
var express = require('express');
var app = express();

app.use(express.static('public/en'));

app.listen(3000, function() {
  console.log('Example app listening on port 3000!');
});
```

Now if you try to access the app via browser, you'll get the error:

```
Failed to decode downloaded font: <URL>
OTS parsing error: invalid version tag
```  

If I modify all files in dist folder, replacing all "url('/assets/" occurrences with "url('/en/assets/", the error disappears. 


